
/*
 * 1. `@.arguments` - This iterator finds the first node named `.arguments` in the current context. It is typically used to access the arguments passed to a function or slot in Hyperlambda.
 * 
 * 2. `*` - This iterator retrieves all children nodes of the `.arguments` node. It is used to access any argument nodes that are direct children of `.arguments`.
 * 
 * 3. `/message` - This iterator filters the result set to only include nodes named `message` among the children of `.arguments`. It is used to specifically access the `message` argument if it exists.
 * 
 * Potential use cases:
 * - This expression can be used in a Hyperlambda slot or endpoint to retrieve the value of a `message` argument passed to it, allowing the slot to process or respond based on the content of the message.
 */

.:x:@.arguments/*/message